one of the missing parts is not using main thread. When you use reloadData of collectionView use with main thread. 

    DispatchQueue.main.async { [weak self] in
        self.collectionView.reloadData()
    }

Then another thing is if you want to process anything in backward controller, I would recommmend you to use `Protocol / Delegates.`

Describe a protocol 

    protocol Handler:class{
        func reloadHandler()
    }

Then extend it with your `MainController`. After extending use your own reload function in protocol&#39;s function.

    extension MainController: Handler{
    
        func reloadHandler() {
                self.reload()
        }
    }

Then delegate the protocol in target `ViewController`

    class TargetController: UIViewController {
        weak var delegate: Handler?
    }

Before the push the targetController, you must assign self to delegate of the `TargetController.`

    var target = TargetController()
    target.delegate = self


You set the delegation between two controllers. Now time to trigger your action. In target controller, when you trigger the `reload()`, use `delegate?.reloadHandler()`.

